                                <p class="font_8">
                                 Students from completed Kindergarten to completed 5th grade are invited to a music camp that will be full of faster than the speed of light fun and an out of this world Biblical message. This Star Wars based music camp will be full of singing, acting, choreography, and set building. There is something for every Jedi. Students must complete the registration and medical release forms, youth volunteers must complete the youth volunteer form and medical release form, and adult volunteers must complete the adult volunteer form only. Click the button for more information and registrations forms.
                                </p>

                                <p class="font_8">
                                 If you have a rising 6th grader, let us welcome them to our JUP Youth Flock! We have a tradition of flocking our new youth with plastic flamingos, a goodie bag, and an invitation to our End of Summer/ Welcome 6th Graders Party on Saturday, August 4th. Flockings will begin the 3rd week of July. Please make sure you contact our Youth Director to get onto the flamingo calendar for the Summer. We are happy to flock older youth as well.
                                </p>
